Name: absolute file path

Synonyms: absolute file path,absolute path,full path,full pathname

Type: glossary

Description:
The full name and location of a <file>, beginning with the disk the <file> is on, including the names of all <folder|folders> that contain the <file> in nested order, and finally the file name itself. 
 
An absolute file path is always the same, regardless of which <folder> is the current <current folder|default folder>.

References: current folder (glossary), file (glossary), folder (glossary)

Tags: file system
